{"word":"μάθησις","slug":"μάθησις","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>μάθησις</b></el> <el>(μάθησις, ιος, ἡ,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:μανθάνω'><el>μανθάνω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>learning, the getting of knowledge</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>desire of learning</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>education, instruction</i>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}